findings.liver: Homogenous attenuation throughout. Subcentimeter hypodensity in segment VII, too small to characterize by CT. No evidence of biliary dilatation.
findings.pancreas: Normal attenuation throughout, no focal lesions or ductal dilatation.
findings.spleen: Normal size and attenuation throughout, no focal lesions.
findings.kidneys: Normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram, no focal lesions or hydronephrosis.
findings.gastrointestinal: Small hiatal hernia, normal caliber small bowel, colon, and rectum. Appendix dilated to 10 mm, fluid-filled, with hyperemic wall and minimal surrounding fat stranding.
findings.bones: No worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
findings.soft tissues: Calcified granulomas overlying the gluteal region bilaterally.

laboratory_examinations.findings: MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
